Debra Arries and her husband Joey started New Version Recycling in their backyard. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - They live in an area notorious for gang violence and unemployment but, the Arries family in Cape Town, is dead-set against becoming a statistic. They have started a recycling business in the heart of Tafelsig in Mitchells Plain. Debra Arries and her husband Joey started New Version Recycling in their backyard. Operating from home, they now employ five young men from Tafelsig. READ:Â Waste pickers key to recycling industry: experts The pair has big dreams of expanding their business but a lack of finances, space and equipment is hampering them. They are also in dire need of a new vehicle to transport their recycled goods more efficiently but for now, they will continue working to keep these streets clean.